[The record of seasonal influenza virus infection follows expectations during the course of the Southern Hemisphere seasonal outbreak. No new antigenic strains have appeared, and the imperfect match of the vaccine strain relevant to the epidemic virus has not had a marked affect. No information regarding the number of antineuraminidase-resistant strains is provided. It seems likely that the vaccine in production for the next winter epidemic will be adequate. In accordance, the ubiquitous pattern in the southern hemisphere epidemic is less severe than the northern hemisphere epidemics.

Up to the present, seasonal influenza remains responsible for the majority of non-lethal respiratory illnesses in the human population - Mod.CP]
